


Introduction
-Appium is an open source tool to automate mobile applications
-It is a cross-platform test automation tool for native, hybrid, and mobile web apps.
-It supports simulators (iOS), emulators (Android), and real devices (iOS, Android, Windows, Mac).
-It supports multiple programming languages.


Desired Capabilities: a set of keys and values sent to Appium server to define what kind of automation session we are interested in starting up.
-The minimum set of required capabilities for any Appium driver should include:

-platformName: the name of the platform to automate
-platformVersion: the version of the platform to automate
-deviceName: the kind of device to automate
-app: the path to the app you want to automate (but use the browserName capability instead in the case of automating a web browser)
-automationName: the name of the driver you wish to use


